{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775903686061,"sessionID":"ses_283e48203ffe2MoE1BSNUnFnFc","part":{"id":"prt_d7c1bb95e001Mqsha6sCXj6xpP","messageID":"msg_d7c1ba5590014sKQZVQq3Pp4P2","sessionID":"ses_283e48203ffe2MoE1BSNUnFnFc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1a9c1f271fed496fa330d1139e0fafc4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 — E2E 集成测试 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-041 — E2E 集成测试 |\n8: | Module | test/e2e |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: E2E Framework Setup (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `test/e2e/framework/` directory structure\n20:   - Purpose: Establish E2E test framework foundation\n21:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/`\n22:   - Verification: `ls -la test/e2e/framework/`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `framework/test_context.go` with TestContext struct\n25:   - Purpose: Define test context with K8s client, HTTP client, cleanup hooks\n26:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/test_context.go`\n27:   - Verification: `go build test/e2e/framework/test_context.go`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Implement `framework/kube_client.go` with Kubernetes client helpers\n30:   - Purpose: Provide K8s client initialization utilities\n31:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/kube_client.go`\n32:   - Verification: `go build test/e2e/framework/kube_client.go`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement `framework/http_client.go` with HTTP test clients\n35:   - Purpose: Create SandboxTestClient, RouterTestClient, PicoDTestClient\n36:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/http_client.go`\n37:   - Verification: `go build test/e2e/framework/http_client.go`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement `framework/wait_helpers.go` with wait utilities\n40:   - Purpose: Provide WaitForPodRunning, WaitForPodDeleted, WaitForSandboxReady\n41:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/wait_helpers.go`\n42:   - Verification: `go build test/e2e/framework/wait_helpers.go`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6**: Implement `framework/fixture_manager.go` for fixture loading\n45:   - Purpose: Load YAML fixtures and manage cleanup\n46:   - File: `test/e2e/framework/fixture_manager.go`\n47:   - Verification: `go build test/e2e/framework/fixture_manager.go`\n48: \n49: ### Phase 2: Test Fixtures Creation (ST-2)\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `test/e2e/fixtures/` directory\n52:   - Purpose: Establish test fixtures repository\n53:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/`\n54:   - Verification: `ls -la test/e2e/fixtures/`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `fixtures/echo_agent.yaml` AgentRuntime fixture\n57:   - Purpose: Provide echo agent for Router invocation tests\n58:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/echo_agent.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/fixtures/echo_agent.yaml --dry-run=client`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` CodeInterpreter fixture\n62:   - Purpose: Provide code interpreter for PicoD execution tests\n63:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml --dry-run=client`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` WarmPool fixture\n67:   - Purpose: Provide warm pool configuration for allocation tests\n68:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml --dry-run=client`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.5**: Create `fixtures/test_data/` directory\n72:   - Purpose: Store test scripts and data files\n73:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/`\n74:   - Verification: `ls -la test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `fixtures/test_data/simple_script.py` test script\n77:   - Purpose: Provide Python script for successful execution tests\n78:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/simple_script.py`\n79:   - Verification: `python3 test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/simple_script.py`\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `fixtures/test_data/error_script.py` error script\n82:   - Purpose: Provide Python script with syntax error for error handling tests\n83:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/error_script.py`\n84:   - Verification: `python3 test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/error_script.py 2>&1 | grep SyntaxError`\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `fixtures/test_data/large_file.txt` large file fixture\n87:   - Purpose: Provide large file for upload/download tests (1MB+)\n88:   - File: `test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/large_file.txt`\n89:   - Verification: `ls -lh test/e2e/fixtures/test_data/large_file.txt | grep -E \"[1-9][0-9]*K|M\"`\n90: \n91: ### Phase 3: E2E Test Suite Entry Point (ST-3)\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `test/e2e/e2e_test.go` TestMain entry point\n94:   - Purpose: Initialize test suite with flags and environment setup\n95:   - File: `test/e2e/e2e_test.go`\n96:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestMain ./test/e2e/ -count=1`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.2**: Add test flags for workload-manager-url, router-url, api-token, namespace\n99:   - Purpose: Configure E2E test environment via flags\n100:   - File: `test/e2e/e2e_test.go`\n101:   - Verification: `go test -v ./test/e2e/ -workload-manager-url=http://localhost:8080 -router-url=http://localhost:8081 -api-token=test -namespace=test`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement test suite registration with cleanup hooks\n104:   - Purpose: Ensure all tests cleanup resources on completion\n105:   - File: `test/e2e/e2e_test.go`\n106:   - Verification: `go test -v ./test/e2e/ -run TestE2ESuite`\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T3.4**: Add Skip condition for short test mode\n109:   - Purpose: Allow skipping E2E tests with `-short` flag\n110:   - File: `test/e2e/e2e_test.go`\n111:   - Verification: `go test -v -short ./test/e2e/ | grep \"skipping\"`\n112: \n113: ### Phase 4: WorkloadManager E2E Tests (ST-4)\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go` TestSandboxCreate\n116:   - Purpose: Verify POST /v1/sandbox creates sandbox pod\n117:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestSandboxCreate ./test/e2e/`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement TestSandboxGet for GET /v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name\n121:   - Purpose: Verify sandbox info retrieval\n122:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n123:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestSandboxGet ./test/e2e/`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement TestSandboxDelete for DELETE /v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name\n126:   - Purpose: Verify sandbox cleanup\n127:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n128:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestSandboxDelete ./test/e2e/`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement TestSandboxIdempotency for repeated creation\n131:   - Purpose: Verify same sessionId returned for same name\n132:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n133:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestSandboxIdempotency ./test/e2e/`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement TestSandboxInvalidInput for validation errors\n136:   - Purpose: Verify 400 response for invalid requests\n137:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n138:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestSandboxInvalidInput ./test/e2e/`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement TestHealthEndpoints for /health/live and /health/ready\n141:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager health probes\n142:   - File: `test/e2e/sandbox_test.go`\n143:   - Verification: `go test -v -run TestHealthEndpoints ./test/e2e/`\n144: \n145: ### Phase 5: Router E2E Tests (ST-5)\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.1**: Implement `test/e2e/router_test.go` TestRouterAuthIntercept\n148:   - Purpose: V