{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775903704098,"sessionID":"ses_283e48203ffe2MoE1BSNUnFnFc","part":{"id":"prt_d7c1bfb61001RiUyDtlRWW9mlT","messageID":"msg_d7c1be33e001jZI54XdmAAW1DU","sessionID":"ses_283e48203ffe2MoE1BSNUnFnFc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5ebe6cf284e44582a85af9b37bc1de2b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test/e2e/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/test/e2e/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n2: \n3: **Module:** test/e2e  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: End-to-end integration tests for AgentCube validate the complete system workflow from sandbox creation through code execution, covering all core components: Workload Manager, Router, and PicoD. Tests run against a real Kubernetes cluster (Kind) with full component deployment.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### Test Environment\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                          E2E Test Environment (Kind Cluster)                      │\n22: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n23: │                                                                                  │\n24: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n25: │  │                        Kubernetes Cluster (agentcube-e2e)                    ││\n26: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐    ││\n27: │  │  │ Workload     │  │   Router     │  │   Redis      │  │   CRDs       │    ││\n28: │  │  │ Manager      │  │  Deployment  │  │  Deployment  │  │  AgentRuntime│    ││\n29: │  │  │ Deployment   │  │              │  │              │  │  CodeInterp. │    ││\n30: │  │  │  (Pod :8080) │  │  (Pod :8080) │  │ (:6379)      │  │              │    ││\n31: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘    ││\n32: │  │         │                 │                  │                              ││\n33: │  │         │                 │                  │                              ││\n34: │  │  ┌──────┴─────────────────┴──────────────────┴──────────────────────────┐  ││\n35: │  │  │                    Agent Sandbox Pods (created by tests)              │  ││\n36: │  │  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │  ││\n37: │  │  │  │ Sandbox Pod                                                       │ │  ││\n38: │  │  │  │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐                         │ │  ││\n39: │  │  │  │  │   PicoD        │  │   Workload     │                         │ │  ││\n40: │  │  │  │  │   Sidecar      │  │   Container    │                         │ │  ││\n41: │  │  │  │  │   (:8080)      │  │   (echo agent) │                         │ │  ││\n42: │  │  │  │  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘                         │ │  ││\n43: │  │  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │  ││\n44: │  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  ││\n45: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n46: │                                                                                  │\n47: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n48: │  │                         Port-Forward (localhost)                            ││\n49: │  │  Workload Manager: localhost:8080 → svc/workloadmanager:8080                ││\n50: │  │  Router:           localhost:8081 → svc/agentcube-router:8080               ││\n51: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n52: │                                                                                  │\n53: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n54: │  │                         Test Runner                                          ││\n55: │  │  - Go test framework (testing package)                                       ││\n56: │  │  - Environment variables: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL, API_TOKEN        ││\n57: │  │  - Python venv for SDK tests                                                 ││\n58: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n59: │                                                                                  │\n60: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Directory Structure\n64: \n65: ```\n66: test/e2e/\n67: ├── design.md                        # This design document\n68: ├── README.md                        # Test execution guide\n69: ├── run_e2e.sh                       # E2E test orchestration script\n70: ├── kind-config.yaml                 # Kind cluster configuration\n71: ├── e2e_test.go                      # Go E2E test suite entry point\n72: ├── sandbox_test.go                  # Sandbox lifecycle tests\n73: ├── session_test.go                  # Session management tests\n74: ├── code_execution_test.go           # Code execution tests\n75: ├── router_test.go                   # Router invocation tests\n76: ├── idle_cleanup_test.go             # Idle cleanup E2E tests\n77: ├── warm_pool_test.go                # Warm pool tests\n78: ├── fixtures/\n79: │   ├── echo_agent.yaml              # Echo AgentRuntime fixture\n80: │   ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml    # CodeInterpreter fixture\n81: │   ├── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml  # WarmPool fixture\n82: │   └── test_data/\n83: │       ├── simple_script.py         # Test Python script\n84: │       ├── error_script.py          # Error-inducing script\n85: │       └── large_file.txt           # Large file upload test\n86: ├── framework/\n87: │   ├── test_context.go              # Test context management\n88: │   ├── kube_client.go               # Kubernetes client helpers\n89: │   ├── http_client.go               # HTTP client helpers\n90: │   ├── wait_helpers.go              # Wait/poll utilities\n91: │   └── fixture_manager.go           # Fixture loading/cleanup\n92: ├── __init__.py                      # Python test package marker\n93: └── test_codeinterpreter.py          # Python SDK E2E tests\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Test Flow Diagram\n97: \n98: ```\n99: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n100: │                          E2E Test Execution Flow                                 │\n101: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n102: │                                                                                  │\n103: │  1. Setup Phase                                                                  │\n104: │  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                   │\n105: │  │ Kind     │───▶│ Build    │───▶│ Load     │───▶│ Deploy   │                   │\n106: │  │ Cluster  │    │ Images   │    │ Images   │    │ Helm     │                   │\n107: │  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                   │\n108: │        │              │              │              │                            │\n109: │        ▼              ▼              ▼              ▼                            │\n110: │  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                   │\n111: │  │ Apply    │───▶│ Wait     │───▶│ Port     │───▶│ Setup    │                   │\n112: │  │ CRDs     │    │ Ready    │    │ Forward  │    │ Auth     │                   │\n113: │  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                   │\n114: │                                                                                  │\n115: │  2. Test Execution Phase                                                         │\n116: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n117: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n118: │  │  │ TestCase-WM-*       │  Workload Manager Tests                            ││\n119: │  │  │  - Sandbox create   │                                                     ││\n120: │  │  │  - Sandbox get      │                                                     ││\n121: │  │  │  - Sandbox delete   │                                                     ││\n122: │  │  │  - Idempotency      │                                                     ││\n123: │  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n124: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n125: │  │  │ TestCase-RT-*       │  Router Tests                                       ││\n126: │  │  │  - Auth intercept   │                                                     ││\n127: │  │  │  - Session routing  │                                                     ││\n128: │  │  │  - Session expiry   │                                                     ││\n129: │  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n130: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n131: │  │  │ TestCase-PD-*       │  PicoD Tests                                        ││\n132: │  │  │  - Python execute   │                                                     ││\n133: │  │  │  - Error handling   │                                                     ││\n134: │  │  │  - File operations  │                                                     ││\n135: │  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n136: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n137: │  │  │ TestCase-ST-*       │  Store Tests                                        ││\n138: │  │  │  - Redis Set/Get    │                                                     ││\n139: │  │  │  - TTL validation   │                                                     ││\n140: │  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n141: │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐                                                     ││\n142: │  │  │ TestCase-SDK-*      │  Python SDK Tests                                   ││\n143: │  │  │  - Context manager  │                                                     ││\n144: │  │  │  - Exception map    │                                                     ││\n145: │  │  └─────────────────────┘                                                     ││\n146: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n147: │                                                                                  │\n148: │  3. Cleanup Phase                                                                │\n149: │  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐                                   │\n150: │  │ Collect  │───▶│ Kill     │───▶│ Delete   │                                   │\n151: │  │ Logs     │    │ Port-Fwd │    │ Cluster  │                                   │\n152: │  └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘                                   │\n153: │                                                                                  │\n154: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Data Structures\n160: \n161: ### TestContext\n162: \n163: ```go\n164: package framework\n165: \n166: type TestContext struct {\n167:     Namespace           string\n168:     WorkloadManagerURL  string\n169:     RouterURL           string\n170:     APIToken            string\n171:     K8sClient           *kubernetes.Clientset\n172:     DynamicClient       dynamic.Interface\n173:     RESTConfig          *rest.Config\n174:     AgentCubeClient     versioned.Interface\n175:     TestID              string\n176:     StartTime           time.Time\n177:     CleanupFuncs        []func()\n178: }\n179: \n180: func NewTestContext(namespace, wmURL, routerURL, apiToken string) (*TestContext, error) {\n181:     config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n182:     if err != nil {\n183:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get in-cluster config: %w\", err)\n184:     }\n185:     \n186:     k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n187:     if err != nil {\n188:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create k8s client: %w\", err)\n189:     }\n190:     \n191:     dynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(config)\n192:     if err != nil {\n193:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create dynamic client: %w\", err)\n194:     }\n195:     \n196:     agentCubeClient, err := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n197:     if err != nil {\n198:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create agentcube client: %w\", err)\n199:     }\n200:     \n201:     return &TestContext{\n202:         Namespace:          namespace,\n203:         WorkloadManagerURL: wmURL,\n204:         RouterURL:          routerURL,\n205:         APIToken:           apiToken,\n206:         K8sClient:          k8sClient,\n207:         DynamicClient:      dynamicClient,\n208:         RESTConfig:         config,\n209:         AgentCubeClient:    agentCubeClient,\n210:         TestID:             uuid.New().String()[:8],\n211:         StartTime:          time.Now(),\n212:         CleanupFuncs:       []func(){},\n213:     }, nil\n214: }\n215: \n216: func (tc *TestContext) AddCleanup(fn func()) {\n217:     tc.CleanupFuncs = append(tc.CleanupFuncs, fn)\n218: }\n219: \n220: func (tc *TestContext) Cleanup() {\n221:     for i := len(tc.CleanupFuncs) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {\n222:         tc.CleanupFuncs[i]()\n223:     }\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### SandboxTestClient\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: package framework\n231: \n232: type SandboxTestClient struct {\n233:     baseURL    string\n234:     httpClient *http.Client\n235:     token      string\n236: }\n237: \n238: func NewSandboxTestClient(baseURL, token string) *SandboxTestClient {\n239:     return &SandboxTestClient{\n240:         baseURL: baseURL,\n241:         httpClient: &http.Client{\n242:             Timeout: 30 * time.Second,\n243:         },\n244:         token: token,\n245:     }\n246: }\n247: \n248: func (c *SandboxTestClient) CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *types.CreateSandboxRequest) (*types.CreateSandboxResponse, error) {\n249:     body, err := json.Marshal(req)\n250:     if err != nil {\n251:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal request: %w\", err)\n252:     }\n253:     \n254:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/v1/sandbox\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n255:     if err != nil {\n256:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create request: %w\", err)\n257:     }\n258:     \n259:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n260:     if c.token != \"\" {\n261:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n262:     }\n263:     \n264:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n265:     if err != nil {\n266:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to send request: %w\", err)\n267:     }\n268:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n269:     \n270:     if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n271:         respBody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n272:         return nil, &APIError{\n273:             StatusCode: resp.StatusCode,\n274:             Body:       string(respBody),\n275:         }\n276:     }\n277:     \n278:     var result types.CreateSandboxResponse\n279:     if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n280:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode response: %w\", err)\n281:     }\n282:     \n283:     return &result, nil\n284: }\n285: \n286: func (c *SandboxTestClient) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n287:     url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/sandbox/%s/%s\", c.baseURL, namespace, name)\n288:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", url, nil)\n289:     if err != nil {\n290:         return nil, err\n291:     }\n292:     \n293:     if c.token != \"\" {\n294:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n295:     }\n296:     \n297:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n298:     if err != nil {\n299:         return nil, err\n300:     }\n301:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n302:     \n303:     var result types.SandboxInfo\n304:     if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n305:         return nil, err\n306:     }\n307:     \n308:     return &result, nil\n309: }\n310: \n311: func (c *SandboxTestClient) DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n312:     url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/sandbox/%s/%s\", c.baseURL, namespace, name)\n313:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"DELETE\", url, nil)\n314:     if err != nil {\n315:         return err\n316:     }\n317:     \n318:     if c.token != \"\" {\n319:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n320:     }\n321:     \n322:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n323:     if err != nil {\n324:         return err\n325:     }\n326:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n327:     \n328:     if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK && resp.StatusCode != http.StatusNoContent {\n329:         return &APIError{StatusCode: resp.StatusCode}\n330:     }\n331:     \n332:     return nil\n333: }\n334: ```\n335: \n336: ### RouterTestClient\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: package framework\n340: \n341: type RouterTestClient struct {\n342:     baseURL    string\n343:     httpClient *http.Client\n344:     token      string\n345: }\n346: \n347: func NewRouterTestClient(baseURL, token string) *RouterTestClient {\n348:     return &RouterTestClient{\n349:         baseURL: baseURL,\n350:         httpClient: &http.Client{\n351:             Timeout: 60 * time.Second,\n352:         },\n353:         token: token,\n354:     }\n355: }\n356: \n357: func (c *RouterTestClient) InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name, path string, body []byte) (*http.Response, error) {\n358:     url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/namespaces/%s/agent-runtimes/%s/invocations%s\", \n359:         c.baseURL, namespace, name, path)\n360:     \n361:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", url, bytes.NewReader(body))\n362:     if err != nil {\n363:         return nil, err\n364:     }\n365:     \n366:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n367:     if c.token != \"\" {\n368:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n369:     }\n370:     \n371:     return c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n372: }\n373: \n374: func (c *RouterTestClient) InvokeCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name, sessionID, path string, body []byte) (*http.Response, error) {\n375:     url := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/namespaces/%s/code-interpreters/%s/invocations%s\",\n376:         c.baseURL, namespace, name, path)\n377:     \n378:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", url, bytes.NewReader(body))\n379:     if err != nil {\n380:         return nil, err\n381:     }\n382:     \n383:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n384:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"x-agentcube-session-id\", sessionID)\n385:     if c.token != \"\" {\n386:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.token)\n387:     }\n388:     \n389:     return c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n390: }\n391: ```\n392: \n393: ### PicoDTestClient\n394: \n395: ```go\n396: package framework\n397: \n398: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n399:     Language string `json:\"language\"`\n400:     Code     string `json:\"code\"`\n401: }\n402: \n403: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n404:     Stdout   string `json:\"stdout\"`\n405:     Stderr   string `json:\"stderr\"`\n406:     ExitCode int    `json:\"exitCode\"`\n407: }\n408: \n409: type PicoDTestClient struct {\n410:     baseURL    string\n411:     httpClient *http.Client\n412:     jwtToken   string\n413: }\n414: \n415: func NewPicoDTestClient(baseURL, jwtToken string) *PicoDTestClient {\n416:     return &PicoDTestClient{\n417:         baseURL: baseURL,\n418:         httpClient: &http.Client{\n419:             Timeout: 120 * time.Second,\n420:         },\n421:         jwtToken: jwtToken,\n422:     }\n423: }\n424: \n425: func (c *PicoDTestClient) Execute(ctx context.Context, req *ExecuteRequest) (*ExecuteResponse, error) {\n426:     body, err := json.Marshal(req)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         return nil, err\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/api/execute\", bytes.NewReader(body))\n432:     if err != nil {\n433:         return nil, err\n434:     }\n435:     \n436:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n437:     if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n438:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n442:     if err != nil {\n443:         return nil, err\n444:     }\n445:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n446:     \n447:     var result ExecuteResponse\n448:     if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n449:         return nil, err\n450:     }\n451:     \n452:     return &result, nil\n453: }\n454: \n455: func (c *PicoDTestClient) UploadFile(ctx context.Context, filename string, content []byte) error {\n456:     body := bytes.NewReader(content)\n457:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"POST\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files?path=\"+filename, body)\n458:     if err != nil {\n459:         return err\n460:     }\n461:     \n462:     httpReq.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/octet-stream\")\n463:     if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n464:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n465:     }\n466:     \n467:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n468:     if err != nil {\n469:         return err\n470:     }\n471:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n472:     \n473:     if resp.StatusCode != http.StatusOK {\n474:         return fmt.Errorf(\"upload failed: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n475:     }\n476:     \n477:     return nil\n478: }\n479: \n480: func (c *PicoDTestClient) ListFiles(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error) {\n481:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files\", nil)\n482:     if err != nil {\n483:         return nil, err\n484:     }\n485:     \n486:     if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n487:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n488:     }\n489:     \n490:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n491:     if err != nil {\n492:         return nil, err\n493:     }\n494:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n495:     \n496:     var result []string\n497:     if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {\n498:         return nil, err\n499:     }\n500:     \n501:     return result, nil\n502: }\n503: \n504: func (c *PicoDTestClient) DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, filename string) ([]byte, error) {\n505:     httpReq, err := http.NewRequestWithContext(ctx, \"GET\", c.baseURL+\"/api/files/\"+filename, nil)\n506:     if err != nil {\n507:         return nil, err\n508:     }\n509:     \n510:     if c.jwtToken != \"\" {\n511:         httpReq.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+c.jwtToken)\n512:     }\n513:     \n514:     resp, err := c.httpClient.Do(httpReq)\n515:     if err != nil {\n516:         return nil, err\n517:     }\n518:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n519:     \n520:     return io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n521: }\n522: ```\n523: \n524: ### APIError\n525: \n526: ```go\n527: package framework\n528: \n529: type APIError struct {\n530:     StatusCode int\n531:     Body       string\n532: }\n533: \n534: func (e *APIError) Error() string {\n535:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"API error: status=%d body=%s\", e.StatusCode, e.Body)\n536: }\n537: \n538: func (e *APIError) IsNotFound() bool {\n539:     return e.StatusCode == http.StatusNotFound\n540: }\n541: \n542: func (e *APIError) IsUnauthorized() bool {\n543:     return e.StatusCode == http.StatusUnauthorized\n544: }\n545: \n546: func (e *APIError) IsBadRequest() bool {\n547:     return e.StatusCode == http.StatusBadRequest\n548: }\n549: ```\n550: \n551: ---\n552: \n553: ## API Contracts\n554: \n555: ### Workload Manager API (E2E Tests)\n556: \n557: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n558: |----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n559: | `/v1/sandbox` | POST | Create sandbox | `200 OK` + `CreateSandboxResponse` |\n560: | `/v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name` | GET | Get sandbox info | `200 OK` + `SandboxInfo` |\n561: | `/v1/sandbox/:namespace/:name` | DELETE | Delete sandbox | `200 OK` or `204 No Content` |\n562: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n563: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` |\n564: \n565: #### CreateSandboxRequest Contract\n566: \n567: ```json\n568: {\n569:     \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime|CodeInterpreter\",\n570:     \"name\": \"string (required)\",\n571:     \"namespace\": \"string (required)\"\n572: }\n573: ```\n574: \n575: #### CreateSandboxResponse Contract\n576: \n577: ```json\n578: {\n579:     \"sessionId\": \"string (UUID format)\",\n580:     \"sandboxId\": \"string (UUID format)\",\n581:     \"sandboxName\": \"string\",\n582:     \"entryPoints\": [\n583:         {\n584:             \"path\": \"string\",\n585:             \"protocol\": \"string\",\n586:             \"endpoint\": \"string (URL)\"\n587:         }\n588:     ]\n589: }\n590: ```\n591: \n592: ### Router API (E2E Tests)\n593: \n594: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n595: |----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n596: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n597: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe | `200 OK` + `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` |\n598: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy | Proxied response or error |\n599: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy | Proxied response or error |\n600: \n601: #### Invocation Headers\n602: \n603: | Header | Required | Description |\n604: |--------|----------|-------------|\n605: | `Authorization` | Yes | Bearer token for auth |\n606: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | For CI | Session identifier |\n607: \n608: ### PicoD API (E2E Tests)\n609: \n610: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Expected Response |\n611: |----------|--------|---------|-------------------|\n612: | `/health` | GET | Health check | `200 OK` |\n613: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code | `200 OK` + `ExecuteResponse` |\n614: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file | `200 OK` |\n615: | `/api/files` | GET | List files | `200 OK` + `[\"file1\", ...]` |\n616: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file | `200 OK` + file content |\n617: \n618: #### ExecuteRequest Contract\n619: \n620: ```json\n621: {\n622:     \"language\": \"python|javascript|typescript\",\n623:     \"code\": \"string (code to execute)\"\n624: }\n625: ```\n626: \n627: #### ExecuteResponse Contract\n628: \n629: ```json\n630: {\n631:     \"stdout\": \"string\",\n632:     \"stderr\": \"string\",\n633:     \"exitCode\": \"integer (0 = success)\"\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: ---\n638: \n639: ## Error Handling\n640: \n641: ### Error Categories in E2E Tests\n642: \n643: | Category | HTTP Status | Test Assertion |\n644: |----------|-------------|----------------|\n645: | `BadRequest` | 400 | Validate error message contains expected field |\n646: | `Unauthorized` | 401 | Validate `401` returned without valid token |\n647: | `NotFound` | 404 | Validate error message contains resource name |\n648: | `Conflict` | 409 | Used for idempotency validation (same sessionId) |\n649: | `InternalError` | 500 | Log and fail test with diagnostics |\n650: | `Timeout` | N/A | Use `WaitFor` with timeout and fail on exceed |\n651: \n652: ### Test Error Handling Pattern\n653: \n654: ```go\n655: func handleTestError(t *testing.T, err error, tc *TestContext) {\n656:     if err == nil {\n657:         return\n658:     }\n659:     \n660:     var apiErr *APIError\n661:     if errors.As(err, &apiErr) {\n662:         t.Logf(\"API Error: status=%d body=%s\", apiErr.StatusCode, apiErr.Body)\n663:         \n664:         if apiErr.StatusCode >= 500 {\n665:             collectComponentLogs(t, tc)\n666:         }\n667:     } else {\n668:         t.Logf(\"Non-API Error: %v\", err)\n669:     }\n670:     \n671:     t.Fail()\n672: }\n673: \n674: func collectComponentLogs(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext) {\n675:     components := []string{\"workloadmanager\", \"router\"}\n676:     for _, comp := range components {\n677:         logs, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n678:             GetLogs(comp, &corev1.PodLogOptions{TailLines: pointer.Int64(100)}).\n679:             DoRaw(context.Background())\n680:         if err == nil {\n681:             t.Logf(\"=== %s logs ===\\n%s\", comp, logs)\n682:         }\n683:     }\n684: }\n685: ```\n686: \n687: ### Retry Pattern for Flaky Operations\n688: \n689: ```go\n690: func RetryWithBackoff(ctx context.Context, op func() error, maxAttempts int, baseDelay time.Duration) error {\n691:     var lastErr error\n692:     for attempt := 0; attempt < maxAttempts; attempt++ {\n693:         err := op()\n694:         if err == nil {\n695:             return nil\n696:         }\n697:         lastErr = err\n698:         \n699:         if !isRetryable(err) {\n700:             return err\n701:         }\n702:         \n703:         delay := baseDelay * time.Duration(1<<attempt)\n704:         select {\n705:         case <-ctx.Done():\n706:             return ctx.Err()\n707:         case <-time.After(delay):\n708:         }\n709:     }\n710:     return fmt.Errorf(\"max attempts exceeded: %w\", lastErr)\n711: }\n712: \n713: func isRetryable(err error) bool {\n714:     var apiErr *APIError\n715:     if errors.As(err, &apiErr) {\n716:         return apiErr.StatusCode >= 500 || apiErr.StatusCode == 429\n717:     }\n718:     return true\n719: }\n720: ```\n721: \n722: ---\n723: \n724: ## Testing Strategy\n725: \n726: ### Test Categories\n727: \n728: | Category | Coverage | Duration |\n729: |----------|----------|----------|\n730: | Workload Manager | Sandbox CRUD, idempotency, warm pool | ~2 min |\n731: | Router | Auth, session routing, proxy | ~3 min |\n732: | PicoD | Execute, files, auth | ~2 min |\n733: | Store | Redis operations, TTL | ~1 min |\n734: | Integration | Full workflow end-to-end | ~5 min |\n735: | Python SDK | Client lifecycle, exceptions | ~2 min |\n736: \n737: ### TestCase-WM-001: Sandbox Creation\n738: \n739: ```go\n740: func TestSandboxCreate(t *testing.T) {\n741:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n742:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n743:     \n744:     client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n745:     \n746:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n747:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n748:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n749:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n750:     }\n751:     \n752:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n753:     defer cancel()\n754:     \n755:     resp, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n756:     require.NoError(t, err)\n757:     \n758:     assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID, \"sessionId should not be empty\")\n759:     assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SandboxID, \"sandboxId should not be empty\")\n760:     assert.Len(t, resp.EntryPoints, 1, \"should have at least one entry point\")\n761:     \n762:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n763:         client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, resp.SandboxName)\n764:     })\n765:     \n766:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n767:         pod, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n768:             Get(context.Background(), resp.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n769:         if err != nil {\n770:             return false\n771:         }\n772:         return pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning\n773:     }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second, \"sandbox pod should become running\")\n774: }\n775: ```\n776: \n777: ### TestCase-WM-002: Idempotency\n778: \n779: ```go\n780: func TestSandboxIdempotency(t *testing.T) {\n781:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n782:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n783:     \n784:     client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n785:     \n786:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n787:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n788:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-idempotent\",\n789:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n790:     }\n791:     \n792:     ctx := context.Background()\n793:     \n794:     resp1, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n795:     require.NoError(t, err)\n796:     \n797:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n798:         client.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, resp1.SandboxName)\n799:     })\n800:     \n801:     resp2, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, req)\n802:     require.NoError(t, err)\n803:     \n804:     assert.Equal(t, resp1.SessionID, resp2.SessionID, \n805:         \"same name should return same sessionId\")\n806:     assert.Equal(t, resp1.SandboxID, resp2.SandboxID,\n807:         \"same name should return same sandboxId\")\n808: }\n809: ```\n810: \n811: ### TestCase-WM-003: Invalid Input\n812: \n813: ```go\n814: func TestSandboxInvalidInput(t *testing.T) {\n815:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n816:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n817:     \n818:     client := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n819:     \n820:     tests := []struct {\n821:         name    string\n822:         request *types.CreateSandboxRequest\n823:         expect  int\n824:     }{\n825:         {\n826:             name: \"missing name\",\n827:             request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n828:                 Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n829:                 Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n830:             },\n831:             expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n832:         },\n833:         {\n834:             name: \"missing namespace\",\n835:             request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n836:                 Kind: types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n837:                 Name: \"test-sandbox\",\n838:             },\n839:             expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n840:         },\n841:         {\n842:             name: \"invalid kind\",\n843:             request: &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n844:                 Kind:      \"InvalidKind\",\n845:                 Name:      \"test-sandbox\",\n846:                 Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n847:             },\n848:             expect: http.StatusBadRequest,\n849:         },\n850:     }\n851:     \n852:     for _, tt := range tests {\n853:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n854:             ctx := context.Background()\n855:             _, err := client.CreateSandbox(ctx, tt.request)\n856:             \n857:             var apiErr *APIError\n858:             require.Error(t, err)\n859:             require.True(t, errors.As(err, &apiErr))\n860:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expect, apiErr.StatusCode)\n861:         })\n862:     }\n863: }\n864: ```\n865: \n866: ### TestCase-RT-001: Auth Intercept\n867: \n868: ```go\n869: func TestRouterAuthIntercept(t *testing.T) {\n870:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n871:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n872:     \n873:     tests := []struct {\n874:         name    string\n875:         token   string\n876:         expect  int\n877:     }{\n878:         {\n879:             name:   \"no token\",\n880:             token:  \"\",\n881:             expect: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n882:         },\n883:         {\n884:             name:   \"invalid token\",\n885:             token:  \"invalid-token\",\n886:             expect: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n887:         },\n888:         {\n889:             name:   \"valid token\",\n890:             token:  tc.APIToken,\n891:             expect: http.StatusOK,\n892:         },\n893:     }\n894:     \n895:     for _, tt := range tests {\n896:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n897:             client := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tt.token)\n898:             \n899:             ctx := context.Background()\n900:             resp, err := client.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent\", \"/\", []byte(\"{}\"))\n901:             require.NoError(t, err)\n902:             defer resp.Body.Close()\n903:             \n904:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expect, resp.StatusCode)\n905:         })\n906:     }\n907: }\n908: ```\n909: \n910: ### TestCase-RT-002: Session Routing\n911: \n912: ```go\n913: func TestRouterSessionRouting(t *testing.T) {\n914:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n915:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n916:     \n917:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n918:     \n919:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n920:         Kind:      types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n921:         Name:      \"echo-agent\",\n922:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n923:     }\n924:     \n925:     sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n926:     require.NoError(t, err)\n927:     \n928:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n929:         wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n930:     })\n931:     \n932:     routerClient := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken)\n933:     \n934:     ctx := context.Background()\n935:     resp, err := routerClient.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent\", \"/echo\", \n936:         []byte(`{\"message\": \"hello e2e\"}`))\n937:     require.NoError(t, err)\n938:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n939:     \n940:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n941:     \n942:     body, err := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n943:     require.NoError(t, err)\n944:     assert.Contains(t, string(body), \"hello e2e\")\n945: }\n946: ```\n947: \n948: ### TestCase-RT-003: Session Expiry\n949: \n950: ```go\n951: func TestRouterSessionExpiry(t *testing.T) {\n952:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n953:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n954:     \n955:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n956:     \n957:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n958:         Kind:      types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n959:         Name:      \"echo-agent-short-ttl\",\n960:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n961:     }\n962:     \n963:     sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n964:     require.NoError(t, err)\n965:     \n966:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n967:         wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n968:     })\n969:     \n970:     routerClient := NewRouterTestClient(tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken)\n971:     \n972:     ctx := context.Background()\n973:     \n974:     time.Sleep(35 * time.Second)\n975:     \n976:     resp, err := routerClient.InvokeAgentRuntime(ctx, tc.Namespace, \"echo-agent-short-ttl\", \"/\", nil)\n977:     require.NoError(t, err)\n978:     defer resp.Body.Close()\n979:     \n980:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusNotFound, resp.StatusCode)\n981: }\n982: ```\n983: \n984: ### TestCase-ST-001: Redis Set/Get\n985: \n986: ```go\n987: func TestStoreRedisSetGet(t *testing.T) {\n988:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n989:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n990:     \n991:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n992:         Addr: fmt.Sprintf(\"redis.%s.svc.cluster.local:6379\", tc.Namespace),\n993:     })\n994:     \n995:     sessionInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n996:         SessionID:        uuid.New().String(),\n997:         SandboxID:        uuid.New().String(),\n998:         SandboxName:      \"test-sandbox\",\n999:         SandboxNamespace: tc.Namespace,\n1000:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n1001:         ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(24 * time.Hour),\n1002:     }\n1003:     \n1004:     key := fmt.Sprintf(\"session:%s\", sessionInfo.SessionID)\n1005:     value, err := json.Marshal(sessionInfo)\n1006:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1007:     \n1008:     ctx := context.Background()\n1009:     err = redisClient.Set(ctx, key, value, 24*time.Hour).Err()\n1010:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1011:     \n1012:     result, err := redisClient.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n1013:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1014:     \n1015:     var retrieved types.SandboxInfo\n1016:     err = json.Unmarshal([]byte(result), &retrieved)\n1017:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1018:     \n1019:     assert.Equal(t, sessionInfo.SessionID, retrieved.SessionID)\n1020:     assert.Equal(t, sessionInfo.SandboxName, retrieved.SandboxName)\n1021: }\n1022: ```\n1023: \n1024: ### TestCase-ST-002: TTL Validation\n1025: \n1026: ```go\n1027: func TestStoreTTLValidation(t *testing.T) {\n1028:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n1029:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n1030:     \n1031:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n1032:         Addr: fmt.Sprintf(\"redis.%s.svc.cluster.local:6379\", tc.Namespace),\n1033:     })\n1034:     \n1035:     sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n1036:     key := fmt.Sprintf(\"session:%s\", sessionID)\n1037:     \n1038:     ctx := context.Background()\n1039:     err := redisClient.Set(ctx, key, \"test-value\", 24*time.Hour).Err()\n1040:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1041:     \n1042:     ttl, err := redisClient.TTL(ctx, key).Result()\n1043:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1044:     \n1045:     assert.GreaterOrEqual(t, ttl.Seconds(), float64(23*time.Hour/1e9))\n1046:     assert.LessOrEqual(t, ttl.Seconds(), float64(24*time.Hour/1e9))\n1047: }\n1048: ```\n1049: \n1050: ### TestCase-PD-001: Python Execute\n1051: \n1052: ```go\n1053: func TestPicoDPythonExecute(t *testing.T) {\n1054:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n1055:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n1056:     \n1057:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n1058:     \n1059:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n1060:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n1061:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n1062:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n1063:     }\n1064:     \n1065:     sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n1066:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1067:     \n1068:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n1069:         wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n1070:     })\n1071:     \n1072:     waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n1073:     \n1074:     jwtToken := getJWTFromRouter(t, tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken, sandbox.SessionID)\n1075:     picodURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s.%s.pod.cluster.local:8080\", \n1076:         sandbox.SandboxName, tc.Namespace)\n1077:     \n1078:     picodClient := NewPicoDTestClient(picodURL, jwtToken)\n1079:     \n1080:     ctx := context.Background()\n1081:     execResp, err := picodClient.Execute(ctx, &ExecuteRequest{\n1082:         Language: \"python\",\n1083:         Code:     `print(\"hello\")`,\n1084:     })\n1085:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1086:     \n1087:     assert.Equal(t, \"hello\\n\", execResp.Stdout)\n1088:     assert.Equal(t, 0, execResp.ExitCode)\n1089:     assert.Empty(t, execResp.Stderr)\n1090: }\n1091: ```\n1092: \n1093: ### TestCase-PD-002: Error Handling\n1094: \n1095: ```go\n1096: func TestPicoDErrorHandling(t *testing.T) {\n1097:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n1098:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n1099:     \n1100:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n1101:     \n1102:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n1103:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n1104:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter\",\n1105:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n1106:     }\n1107:     \n1108:     sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n1109:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1110:     \n1111:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n1112:         wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), tc.Namespace, sandbox.SandboxName)\n1113:     })\n1114:     \n1115:     waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n1116:     \n1117:     jwtToken := getJWTFromRouter(t, tc.RouterURL, tc.APIToken, sandbox.SessionID)\n1118:     picodURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s.%s.pod.cluster.local:8080\", \n1119:         sandbox.SandboxName, tc.Namespace)\n1120:     \n1121:     picodClient := NewPicoDTestClient(picodURL, jwtToken)\n1122:     \n1123:     ctx := context.Background()\n1124:     execResp, err := picodClient.Execute(ctx, &ExecuteRequest{\n1125:         Language: \"python\",\n1126:         Code:     `import syntax_error`,\n1127:     })\n1128:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1129:     \n1130:     assert.NotEqual(t, 0, execResp.ExitCode)\n1131:     assert.Contains(t, execResp.Stderr, \"SyntaxError\")\n1132: }\n1133: ```\n1134: \n1135: ### TestCase-SDK-001: Context Manager\n1136: \n1137: ```go\n1138: func TestSDKContextManager(t *testing.T) {\n1139:     if testing.Short() {\n1140:         t.Skip(\"skipping SDK test in short mode\")\n1141:     }\n1142:     \n1143:     venvDir := os.Getenv(\"E2E_VENV_DIR\")\n1144:     if venvDir == \"\" {\n1145:         venvDir = \"/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv\"\n1146:     }\n1147:     \n1148:     pythonCmd := filepath.Join(venvDir, \"bin\", \"python\")\n1149:     \n1150:     code := `\n1151: import agentcube\n1152: import sys\n1153: \n1154: created_session_id = None\n1155: \n1156: with agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient(\n1157:     workload_manager_url=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}\",\n1158:     router_url=\"${ROUTER_URL}\",\n1159:     api_token=\"${API_TOKEN}\",\n1160:     namespace=\"${NAMESPACE}\"\n1161: ) as client:\n1162:     created_session_id = client.session_id\n1163:     print(f\"Session created: {created_session_id}\")\n1164:     \n1165:     result = client.execute(language=\"python\", code=\"print('test')\")\n1166:     print(f\"Execution result: {result.stdout}\")\n1167: \n1168: print(\"Context closed\")\n1169: \n1170: sys.exit(0)\n1171: `\n1172:     \n1173:     envVars := fmt.Sprintf(`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=%s ROUTER_URL=%s API_TOKEN=%s NAMESPACE=%s`,\n1174:         os.Getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n1175:         os.Getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"),\n1176:         os.Getenv(\"API_TOKEN\"),\n1177:         os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"))\n1178:     \n1179:     cmd := exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), pythonCmd, \"-c\", code)\n1180:     cmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), strings.Split(envVars, \" \")...)\n1181:     \n1182:     output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n1183:     require.NoError(t, err, \"Python output: %s\", output)\n1184:     \n1185:     assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Session created:\")\n1186:     assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Context closed\")\n1187: }\n1188: ```\n1189: \n1190: ### TestCase-SDK-002: Exception Mapping\n1191: \n1192: ```go\n1193: func TestSDKExceptionMapping(t *testing.T) {\n1194:     if testing.Short() {\n1195:         t.Skip(\"skipping SDK test in short mode\")\n1196:     }\n1197:     \n1198:     venvDir := os.Getenv(\"E2E_VENV_DIR\")\n1199:     if venvDir == \"\" {\n1200:         venvDir = \"/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv\"\n1201:     }\n1202:     \n1203:     pythonCmd := filepath.Join(venvDir, \"bin\", \"python\")\n1204:     \n1205:     code := `\n1206: import agentcube\n1207: import sys\n1208: \n1209: try:\n1210:     client = agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient(\n1211:         workload_manager_url=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}\",\n1212:         router_url=\"${ROUTER_URL}\",\n1213:         api_token=\"invalid-token\",\n1214:         namespace=\"${NAMESPACE}\"\n1215:     )\n1216:     client.execute(language=\"python\", code=\"print('test')\")\n1217: except agentcube.AgentCubeError as e:\n1218:     print(f\"Caught AgentCubeError: {type(e).__name__}\")\n1219:     print(f\"Message: {e.message}\")\n1220:     sys.exit(0)\n1221: except Exception as e:\n1222:     print(f\"Caught unexpected exception: {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\n1223:     sys.exit(1)\n1224: \n1225: sys.exit(1)\n1226: `\n1227:     \n1228:     envVars := fmt.Sprintf(`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=%s ROUTER_URL=%s NAMESPACE=%s`,\n1229:         os.Getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n1230:         os.Getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"),\n1231:         os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"))\n1232:     \n1233:     cmd := exec.CommandContext(context.Background(), pythonCmd, \"-c\", code)\n1234:     cmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), strings.Split(envVars, \" \")...)\n1235:     \n1236:     output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n1237:     require.NoError(t, err, \"Python output: %s\", output)\n1238:     \n1239:     assert.Contains(t, string(output), \"Caught AgentCubeError\")\n1240: }\n1241: ```\n1242: \n1243: ### Warm Pool Tests\n1244: \n1245: ```go\n1246: func TestWarmPoolCreation(t *testing.T) {\n1247:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n1248:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n1249:     \n1250:     applyFixture(t, tc, \"fixtures/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\")\n1251:     \n1252:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n1253:         pods, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(\"default\").\n1254:             List(context.Background(), metav1.ListOptions{\n1255:                 LabelSelector: \"agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool=e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool\",\n1256:             })\n1257:         if err != nil {\n1258:             return false\n1259:         }\n1260:         return len(pods.Items) >= 2\n1261:     }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second, \"warm pool should have 2 ready pods\")\n1262:     \n1263:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n1264:     \n1265:     startTime := time.Now()\n1266:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n1267:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n1268:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-warmpool\",\n1269:         Namespace: \"default\",\n1270:     }\n1271:     \n1272:     resp, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n1273:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1274:     \n1275:     allocationTime := time.Since(startTime)\n1276:     assert.Less(t, allocationTime.Seconds(), 5.0, \n1277:         \"warm pool allocation should be fast (<5s)\")\n1278:     \n1279:     tc.AddCleanup(func() {\n1280:         wmClient.DeleteSandbox(context.Background(), \"default\", resp.SandboxName)\n1281:     })\n1282: }\n1283: ```\n1284: \n1285: ### Idle Cleanup E2E Test\n1286: \n1287: ```go\n1288: func TestIdleCleanupE2E(t *testing.T) {\n1289:     tc := setupTestContext(t)\n1290:     defer tc.Cleanup()\n1291:     \n1292:     wmClient := NewSandboxTestClient(tc.WorkloadManagerURL, tc.APIToken)\n1293:     \n1294:     req := &types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n1295:         Kind:      types.CodeInterpreterKind,\n1296:         Name:      \"e2e-code-interpreter-idle\",\n1297:         Namespace: tc.Namespace,\n1298:     }\n1299:     \n1300:     sandbox, err := wmClient.CreateSandbox(context.Background(), req)\n1301:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1302:     \n1303:     waitForPodRunning(t, tc, sandbox.SandboxName)\n1304:     \n1305:     time.Sleep(16 * time.Minute)\n1306:     \n1307:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n1308:         _, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n1309:             Get(context.Background(), sandbox.SandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n1310:         return apierrors.IsNotFound(err)\n1311:     }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second, \"idle sandbox should be cleaned up\")\n1312: }\n1313: ```\n1314: \n1315: ---\n1316: \n1317: ## Test Execution\n1318: \n1319: ### Environment Variables\n1320: \n1321: | Variable | Required | Description |\n1322: |----------|----------|-------------|\n1323: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | Workload Manager endpoint (e.g., `http://localhost:8080`) |\n1324: | `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint (e.g., `http://localhost:8081`) |\n1325: | `API_TOKEN` | Yes | Kubernetes service account token |\n1326: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Yes | Namespace for test resources (default: `agentcube`) |\n1327: | `E2E_VENV_DIR` | No | Python venv directory for SDK tests |\n1328: | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP` | No | Skip cluster setup if `true` |\n1329: | `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER` | No | Clean cluster before/after tests |\n1330: \n1331: ### Test Runner Script\n1332: \n1333: ```bash\n1334: #!/bin/bash\n1335: set -euo pipefail\n1336: \n1337: E2E_CLUSTER_NAME=\"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME:-agentcube-e2e}\"\n1338: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT=\"${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT:-8080}\"\n1339: ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT=\"${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT:-8081}\"\n1340: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-agentcube}\"\n1341: \n1342: cleanup() {\n1343:     kill $PORT_FORWARD_WM_PID $PORT_FORWARD_ROUTER_PID || true\n1344:     kind delete cluster --name \"$E2E_CLUSTER_NAME\" || true\n1345: }\n1346: \n1347: trap cleanup EXIT\n1348: \n1349: go test -v ./test/e2e/... \\\n1350:     -timeout 30m \\\n1351:     -count=1 \\\n1352:     -workload-manager-url=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n1353:     -router-url=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n1354:     -api-token=\"$API_TOKEN\" \\\n1355:     -namespace=\"$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"\n1356: ```\n1357: \n1358: ### Go Test Flags\n1359: \n1360: ```go\n1361: var (\n1362:     workloadManagerURL = flag.String(\"workload-manager-url\", \"\", \"Workload Manager URL\")\n1363:     routerURL          = flag.String(\"router-url\", \"\", \"Router URL\")\n1364:     apiToken           = flag.String(\"api-token\", \"\", \"API token for authentication\")\n1365:     namespace          = flag.String(\"namespace\", \"agentcube\", \"Test namespace\")\n1366: )\n1367: \n1368: func TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n1369:     flag.Parse()\n1370:     \n1371:     if *workloadManagerURL == \"\" || *routerURL == \"\" || *apiToken == \"\" {\n1372:         fmt.Println(\"Required flags: -workload-manager-url, -router-url, -api-token\")\n1373:         os.Exit(1)\n1374:     }\n1375:     \n1376:     os.Exit(m.Run())\n1377: }\n1378: ```\n1379: \n1380: ---\n1381: \n1382: ## Wait Helpers\n1383: \n1384: ```go\n1385: package framework\n1386: \n1387: func WaitForPodRunning(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, podName string) {\n1388:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n1389:         pod, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n1390:             Get(context.Background(), podName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n1391:         if err != nil {\n1392:             return false\n1393:         }\n1394:         return pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning\n1395:     }, 120*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n1396: }\n1397: \n1398: func WaitForPodDeleted(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, podName string) {\n1399:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n1400:         _, err := tc.K8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(tc.Namespace).\n1401:             Get(context.Background(), podName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n1402:         return apierrors.IsNotFound(err)\n1403:     }, 60*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n1404: }\n1405: \n1406: func WaitForSandboxReady(t *testing.T, tc *TestContext, sandboxName string) {\n1407:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n1408:         sandbox, err := tc.AgentCubeClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().\n1409:             Sandboxes(tc.Namespace).\n1410:             Get(context.Background(), sandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n1411:         if err != nil {\n1412:             return false\n1413:         }\n1414:         return sandbox.Status.Phase == \"Ready\"\n1415:     }, 120*time.Second, 2*time.Second)\n1416: }\n1417: \n1418: func WaitForServiceEndpoint(t *testing.T, baseURL string) {\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1418. Use offset=1419 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEnd-to-end integration tests for AgentCube validate the 